find,locate & grep
GREP:
grep is used to search for a word
grep-n "word" filename
grep -in "word" fileanme
grep -c "word" filename
grep -ic "word" filename
grep -in -e "word" -e "word" -e "word" filename(srch multiple wrds)
grep -in "word" filename filename(srch a word in multiple files)
grep -in -e "word"-e "word" filename filename(srch multiple words in multiple files)
ex: getent passwd |grep -i "root"
FIND: used to search for a file.
find path -name filename(path - flodername)
find . -type f -name filename
find . -tye d -name directory name
LOCATE:
locate filename
